-- Almarai Co., Jarir Marketing: Saudi Arabia Equity Preview
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2012-04-07T07:56:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-07/almarai-co-jarir-marketing-saudi-arabia-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
be active in  Saudi Arabia ’s market. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are from the last close.  The  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  declined 0.4 percent to
7,895.36 on April 4.  Almarai Co. (ALMARAI)  : Saudi Arabia’s largest food
producer by market value reported a 2.9 percent increase in
first-quarter profit to 242.1 million riyals ($65 million) as
sales increased on expansion in the  Persian Gulf . The stock
advanced 0.4 percent to 71.75 riyals.  Jarir Marketing Co. (JARIR)  : Saudi Arabia’s largest
stationery and electronic products retailer said its first-
quarter profit increased 20 percent to 164.2 million riyals on
higher sales of laptops and smart phones. The shares declined
0.3 percent to 154.25 riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
